---
import '../styles/globals.css';

const updated = 'June 14, 2026';
---

<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth font-sans">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
    <title>Privacy Policy — SnapDog</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Privacy Policy for SnapDog Client, snapdog.cc, demo.snapdog.cc, and SnapDog downloads."
    />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a] text-neutral-200 selection:bg-amber-500/20 selection:text-amber-200">
    <main class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-3xl flex-col gap-10 px-5 py-10 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
      <header class="flex flex-col gap-5 border-b border-white/10 pb-8">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex w-fit items-center gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-400 transition-colors hover:text-amber-400">
          <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" class="h-9 w-9" />
          <span>SnapDog</span>
        </a>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-400">Privacy Policy</p>
          <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">Last updated: {updated}</p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5 p-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-200 sm:p-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white">Short Version</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SnapDog is designed to work without accounts, analytics, advertising, tracking, or crash-reporting SDKs.
          In normal use, SnapDogRocks does not receive your room names, server addresses, API keys, playback state,
          music metadata, or settings. The app talks to the SnapDog server you choose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="privacy-content flex flex-col gap-9 text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
        <section>
          <h2>1. Controller</h2>
          <p>The controller responsible for this Privacy Policy is:</p>
          <address>
            Dr. Fabian Schmieder<br />
            c/o lexICT GmbH<br />
            Eichenbrink 5<br />
            30453 Hannover<br />
            Germany
          </address>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@snapdog.cc">hello@snapdog.cc</a></p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Scope</h2>
          <p>This Privacy Policy applies to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>the SnapDog Client mobile apps;</li>
            <li>the website <a href="https://snapdog.cc">snapdog.cc</a>;</li>
            <li>the optional demo service at <a href="https://demo.snapdog.cc">demo.snapdog.cc</a>;</li>
            <li>downloads served from <a href="https://updates.snapdog.cc">updates.snapdog.cc</a>.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. SnapDog Client App</h2>
          <p>
            The SnapDog Client app can be used without a SnapDog account and without any external service operated by us.
            In normal operation, the app connects only to the SnapDog server selected by you, for example a server in
            your home network.
          </p>
          <p>The app may process data locally on your device or with your own SnapDog server, such as:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>server addresses, hostnames, ports, and authentication tokens configured by you;</li>
            <li>room, zone, client, and device names;</li>
            <li>volume, mute, playback, grouping, equalizer, and DSP settings;</li>
            <li>music metadata such as track title, artist, album, playlist, and artwork URLs;</li>
            <li>technical status and error messages from your SnapDog server.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            These data are not sent to SnapDogRocks unless you explicitly connect the app to a service operated by us,
            such as the optional demo described below. The app does not include analytics, advertising, tracking,
            crash-reporting, or profiling SDKs.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Optional Demo Service</h2>
          <p>
            You may choose to connect the app to <a href="https://demo.snapdog.cc">demo.snapdog.cc</a>. The demo exists
            to help app-store reviewers and users understand SnapDog without running their own server.
          </p>
          <p>
            The demo uses mock data only. You cannot enter free-form personal content. Interactions such as play, pause,
            volume, and zone changes are kept in memory and are lost when the virtual machine restarts. The demo
            application does not write access logs.
          </p>
          <p>
            To deliver the demo securely, technically necessary connection data may be processed transiently during your
            HTTPS or WebSocket connection. This may include your IP address, the time of the request, TLS/HTTP/WebSocket
            metadata, and user-agent or app-version information if sent by your client.
          </p>
          <p>
            The legal basis is our legitimate interest in providing a secure, functional demo service
            (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR). The demo is hosted by Render Services, Inc., which acts as our processor under a data
            processing addendum.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Website</h2>
          <p>
            The website <a href="https://snapdog.cc">snapdog.cc</a> is a static website. It does not provide user
            accounts, contact forms, comments, newsletter signup, analytics, advertising, tracking pixels, or cookies.
            Fonts are hosted locally; the website does not load Google Fonts from Google servers.
          </p>
          <p>
            When you visit the website, technically necessary connection data are processed to deliver the page and keep
            it secure. This may include your IP address, the time of the request, requested URL, referrer if sent by your
            browser, user-agent, and similar technical metadata.
          </p>
          <p>
            The legal basis is our legitimate interest in operating a secure and reliable website (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
            The website is hosted by Vercel Inc. on a Pro plan. Vercel acts as our processor under its data processing
            addendum.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Downloads</h2>
          <p>
            Downloads from <a href="https://updates.snapdog.cc">updates.snapdog.cc</a> are delivered through Cloudflare
            as a CDN. When you download a file, technically necessary connection data are processed to deliver the file,
            protect the service, and maintain availability. This may include your IP address, request time, requested
            file, user-agent, and related network metadata.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not use these downloads for advertising or user profiling. Cloudflare acts as a processor where it
            processes personal data on our behalf for the CDN service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. External Links</h2>
          <p>
            Our website and documentation link to external services such as GitHub, GNU, Creative Commons, Spinorama, or
            other project resources. These services are not contacted merely because you visit snapdog.cc. They are
            contacted only if you open the external link. The privacy practices of those services are governed by their
            own policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Service Providers</h2>
          <p>We use the following service providers for hosting and delivery:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Vercel Inc. for hosting <a href="https://snapdog.cc">snapdog.cc</a>;</li>
            <li>Render Services, Inc. for hosting the optional demo service;</li>
            <li>Cloudflare, Inc. for CDN delivery of downloads from <a href="https://updates.snapdog.cc">updates.snapdog.cc</a>.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            These providers may process technical connection data as necessary to provide their services, maintain
            security, prevent abuse, and ensure availability. Where required, we use data processing agreements under
            Art. 28 GDPR and appropriate safeguards for international transfers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Retention</h2>
          <p>
            The SnapDog Client app does not transmit normal-use app data to us. The optional demo keeps mock interaction
            state only in memory and does not persist it. We do not operate our own analytics or tracking logs for the
            app or website.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our processors may retain technically necessary service, security, or abuse-prevention data according to
            their own infrastructure and data processing terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. International Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Some of our processors are based in, or may process data in, countries outside the European Economic Area.
            Where personal data are transferred internationally, we rely on appropriate safeguards such as EU Standard
            Contractual Clauses, data processing agreements, and the providers' technical and organizational measures.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Subject to the conditions of the GDPR, you may have the right to request access, rectification, erasure,
            restriction of processing, data portability, and objection to processing based on legitimate interests.
          </p>
          <p>
            You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a competent data protection supervisory authority. To
            exercise your rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@snapdog.cc">hello@snapdog.cc</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. App Store and Play Store Notes</h2>
          <p>
            SnapDog Client is intended to work without collecting personal data for SnapDogRocks in normal use. The app
            does not track users across apps or websites and does not sell or share personal data for advertising.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you choose to use the optional demo service, only technically necessary connection data are processed
            transiently to provide the connection. The demo contains mock data only and does not accept personal content.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy when SnapDog, our infrastructure, or applicable legal requirements change.
            The date at the top of this page indicates the latest version.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>

    <style>
      .privacy-content h2 {
        color: #ffffff;
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: 1.375rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      }

      .privacy-content p + p,
      .privacy-content p + ul,
      .privacy-content ul + p,
      .privacy-content address + p {
        margin-top: 0.85rem;
      }

      .privacy-content ul {
        list-style: disc;
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
      }

      .privacy-content li + li {
        margin-top: 0.35rem;
      }

      .privacy-content a {
        color: #f59e0b;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.45);
        text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
      }

      .privacy-content a:hover {
        color: #fbbf24;
      }

      .privacy-content address {
        color: #f5f5f5;
        font-style: normal;
        margin-top: 0.85rem;
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
